doc.after: With the bill suitably amended to remove the monopoly provisions the Australian National Airways Commission came into existence in February 1946 The commissioners themselves were prominent high achievers including the director general of civil aviation the deputy director a Labor party luminary and former member of the Commonwealth Bank board the director general of posts and telegraphs and the assistant secretary of the Treasury The Commission was to be chaired by Arthur Coles
